WEBVTT

00:01.034 --> 00:03.068
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

00:21.955 --> 00:23.622
(RAPID GUNFIRE)

00:30.030 --> 00:32.031
Oh, please.

00:33.934 --> 00:38.137
It would take a millennia
for your petty weapons
to hurt me.

00:38.672 --> 00:40.906
(ALL EXCLAIMING)

00:40.941 --> 00:45.844
And I do not have
that kind of time
to waste on you.

00:45.879 --> 00:47.145
(BEEPING)

00:47.180 --> 00:48.614
Make time.

00:50.684 --> 00:51.917
Batman.

00:51.952 --> 00:55.521
I thought they'd send
someone more challenging.

00:57.257 --> 00:59.425
Surrender, Luthor.
(GRUNTS)

01:02.129 --> 01:03.362
(GRUNTS)

01:06.066 --> 01:07.699
Give it your best shot.

01:07.734 --> 01:08.734
Gladly.

01:12.672 --> 01:13.672
(RUMBLING)

01:13.707 --> 01:15.240
(PEOPLE EXCLAIMING)

01:17.077 --> 01:19.144
(GRUNTING)
Quickly, go, go!

01:20.480 --> 01:21.513
(GASPS)

01:24.751 --> 01:25.751
(GRUNTS)

01:33.960 --> 01:35.494
I think you're through,
Luthor.

01:35.529 --> 01:37.696
You would,
you dunder-headed troglodyte.

01:37.731 --> 01:38.730
(BEEPS)

01:43.837 --> 01:44.970
Nice try, Luthor.

01:45.005 --> 01:46.538
But I've played this game.

01:47.707 --> 01:48.874
(INHALING)

02:02.856 --> 02:04.656
(COUGHING)

02:04.691 --> 02:08.093
Power down, before we
rip off the suit for you.

02:08.128 --> 02:11.396
Oh, uh,
you and what army, Batman?

02:11.431 --> 02:13.431
SUPERMAN: This one.

02:13.466 --> 02:15.400
Back so soon?
(CHUCKLES)

02:15.435 --> 02:18.570
I am baffled
you made it back at all.

02:19.472 --> 02:20.472
Ugh.

02:23.009 --> 02:24.209
(GROANS)

02:27.747 --> 02:28.547
Superman.

02:28.582 --> 02:29.915
What's the matter, Superman?

02:29.950 --> 02:33.752
Did my gas leave a bad taste
in your mouth?

02:33.787 --> 02:37.656
(LAUGHS) It's so vile and fun.
Still fun.

02:42.896 --> 02:44.362
It's not good.

02:44.397 --> 02:47.365
He remains unconscious
and his vitals are dipping.

02:47.400 --> 02:49.968
Something is taking down
Superman from the inside.

02:50.003 --> 02:53.172
It's actually
quite fascinating,
if you think about it.

02:54.174 --> 02:55.541
What is it?

02:57.777 --> 03:00.812
It's a nanobot swarm.
Really nasty bugs, too.

03:00.847 --> 03:03.582
They're constructing
a colony in his heart.

03:03.617 --> 03:05.984
Gross, right?
Luthor's no slouch.

03:06.019 --> 03:09.854
These guys are harvesting
the solar energy stored
in Superman's cells.

03:09.889 --> 03:11.890
Ready for more bad news?

03:11.925 --> 03:13.225
Here's their queen.

03:13.260 --> 03:15.360
She's single-handedly
birthing an army.

03:15.395 --> 03:17.462
WONDER WOMAN:
I saw this in a movie once.

03:17.497 --> 03:19.965
And she wasn't
a good mother either.

03:20.000 --> 03:23.868
We stop these bots
and take out their queen.

03:23.903 --> 03:29.307
To do that, we're gonna
have to go inside
as a surgical team.

03:29.342 --> 03:31.643
LEX: Now this is my kind
of medical show.

03:31.678 --> 03:34.980
Live streaming
from the bloodstream.
(CHUCKLES)

03:35.015 --> 03:36.982
Look at those vitals plummet.

03:37.017 --> 03:41.786
According to my calculations,
Superman will be finished
within the hour.

03:41.821 --> 03:42.988
Teatime.

03:46.626 --> 03:48.994
We'll need these to travel
through the bloodstream.

03:52.032 --> 03:53.865
(STEAM HISSES)

03:53.900 --> 03:56.935
These devices
will allow me to extend
my shrinking power to you.

03:56.970 --> 03:59.004
I wish I could
bring you along, Red Tornado,

03:59.039 --> 04:00.905
but this tech
doesn't work well on robots.

04:00.940 --> 04:02.941
Story of my life.

04:02.976 --> 04:04.809
Also, fun fact.

04:04.844 --> 04:08.313
This device can't keep you
microscopic for any longer
than 30 minutes.

04:08.348 --> 04:10.115
And if we're not out by then?

04:10.150 --> 04:12.684
Then it's gonna get
awfully cramped inside
the Man of Steel.

04:12.719 --> 04:16.688
Okay, if everyone's ready,
we'll have to get small.

04:17.590 --> 04:18.624
(BEEPS)

04:28.968 --> 04:31.836
Laser sword with
just a pinch of
kryptonite energy.

04:31.871 --> 04:34.840
Great for hacking through
super nose hairs.

04:38.611 --> 04:41.212
-WONDER WOMAN: Is that...
-Yep. Super booger.

04:41.247 --> 04:42.447
Big one, too.

04:44.150 --> 04:45.584
-(BEEPS)
-Get down.

04:48.355 --> 04:51.523
Ugh. I am sending Luthor
my dry cleaning bill.

04:51.558 --> 04:53.325
Ugh. This is awkward.

04:53.360 --> 04:55.527
Ha. At least
you're not dating him.

04:55.562 --> 04:56.961
What did you say?

04:56.996 --> 04:59.664
Uh, we should get going.

04:59.699 --> 05:04.235
BATMAN: We'll take the sinuses
into the lungs and get into
the bloodstream from there.

05:04.270 --> 05:05.504
Going down.

05:06.339 --> 05:07.906
(MACHINE TRILLING)

05:12.479 --> 05:14.046
(PULSATING)

05:16.716 --> 05:19.618
That's the machine sucking up
Superman's solar energy.

05:22.355 --> 05:24.056
Then it's time to operate.

05:25.191 --> 05:26.458
(GRUNTING)

05:28.027 --> 05:29.428
(STRAINING)

05:32.966 --> 05:33.965
(GRUNTS)

05:39.472 --> 05:41.907
Say goodbye
to your little friends.

05:45.478 --> 05:46.778
(GRUNTING)

05:54.020 --> 05:55.754
(CRACKLING)

05:59.125 --> 06:00.191
It's working.

06:00.226 --> 06:01.993
His vitals are
ticking upwards.

06:02.028 --> 06:03.094
LEX: Impossible.

06:03.129 --> 06:04.929
How is he convalescing?

06:04.964 --> 06:06.297
(MACHINE BEEPING)

06:06.332 --> 06:07.532
Of course.

06:07.567 --> 06:10.602
He must have
some tiny assistance.

06:10.637 --> 06:15.039
Well, I'll have to do
something about that, won't I?

06:15.074 --> 06:16.708
ATOM: Toss those parts
into the bloodstream

06:16.743 --> 06:18.777
so his immune system
can dissolve it.

06:23.149 --> 06:24.616
Their queen is close.

06:26.786 --> 06:29.054
You think she'll mind
if I don't curtsy?

06:35.195 --> 06:36.227
There she is.

06:36.262 --> 06:37.729
Mother of the year.

06:43.436 --> 06:45.036
(CHITTERING)

06:46.406 --> 06:48.140
(GROWLING)

06:50.076 --> 06:52.177
She's leaving.
Was it something I said?

06:52.212 --> 06:54.779
Bet she's looking for
a safer nesting ground.

06:54.814 --> 06:55.947
BATMAN: We can't lose her.

06:55.982 --> 06:58.150
We only have
five minutes left.

07:03.289 --> 07:04.656
(GLASS SHATTERING)

07:04.691 --> 07:07.225
Bad guy here.
(LAUGHS)

07:07.260 --> 07:08.993
Anybody home?

07:09.028 --> 07:10.462
(RED TORNADO GRUNTS)

07:16.503 --> 07:17.702
(GRUNTS)

07:21.040 --> 07:22.474
(SHUDDERING)

07:22.876 --> 07:23.875
(GRUNTS)

07:25.645 --> 07:27.612
I thought that would
knock the wind out of you.

07:31.451 --> 07:33.652
-(DEVICE BEEPING)
-The Watchtower's
been breached.

07:36.589 --> 07:38.189
LEX: Unconscious.

07:38.224 --> 07:39.558
Unprotected.

07:40.460 --> 07:43.528
How unfortunate for you.

07:44.931 --> 07:45.964
(GRUNTS)

07:45.999 --> 07:47.499
(ALL GROANING)

07:48.868 --> 07:51.102
What was that?
A seizure?

07:51.704 --> 07:52.737
It's Luthor.

07:52.772 --> 07:54.372
He's in the Watchtower.

07:54.407 --> 07:57.542
I'll go.
We need all your power
to catch that queen.

07:57.577 --> 07:59.511
You'll only have
three minutes.

07:59.546 --> 08:00.745
Let's move.

08:03.483 --> 08:06.084
-Big mamma up ahead.
-(SCREECHING)

08:13.893 --> 08:14.893
(GRUNTS)

08:18.498 --> 08:19.698
(GRUNTS)

08:24.304 --> 08:25.704
(MOANING)

08:28.541 --> 08:30.608
(BOTH GRUNT)

08:30.643 --> 08:33.511
Holy Aeolus.
Who turned on the fans?

08:33.546 --> 08:35.146
BATMAN: We're in his lungs.

08:37.050 --> 08:39.551
We've got less
than two minutes
to get out of here.

08:40.920 --> 08:41.920
(GRUNTS)

08:45.525 --> 08:47.325
Back off, bug.

08:47.360 --> 08:48.593
(SCREECHING)

08:53.066 --> 08:54.266
(GRUNTING)

08:57.103 --> 09:01.206
I should've known
Superman's breath
was super fresh!

09:04.677 --> 09:07.145
LEX: You won't take this
from me, you little nut.

09:11.751 --> 09:12.951
(INHALES)

09:15.688 --> 09:18.323
His immune system
is attacking us.

09:18.358 --> 09:19.657
(GRUNTS)

09:19.692 --> 09:22.026
It thinks we're a disease.

09:22.061 --> 09:23.061
(BEEPS)

09:31.604 --> 09:33.371
(SCREECHING)

09:33.406 --> 09:34.940
(WONDER WOMAN GROANING)

09:44.317 --> 09:46.051
(STRAINING)

09:49.355 --> 09:51.322
Now, to disinfect this place.

09:51.357 --> 09:52.791
(GRUNTING)

09:57.430 --> 09:58.797
(CRACKLING)

10:01.601 --> 10:02.801
(GRUNTING)

10:10.143 --> 10:12.577
That's one disease
that won't be coming back.

10:12.612 --> 10:14.679
We've got less
than 15 seconds.

10:16.983 --> 10:18.850
It's too far.
We'll never make it.

10:18.885 --> 10:20.652
Maybe this'll help.

10:22.388 --> 10:23.388
(GRUNTS)

10:24.957 --> 10:29.394
How can one infinitesimal imp
cause such big problems?

10:29.429 --> 10:30.996
(SUPERMAN GROANS)

10:31.631 --> 10:33.298
(SNEEZING)

10:35.301 --> 10:36.934
(ALL GRUNT)

10:36.969 --> 10:39.470
You've just been
quarantined, Luthor.

10:39.505 --> 10:40.705
(GROANS)

10:41.374 --> 10:42.841
(SNIFFLING)

10:43.910 --> 10:45.710
Uh, what's going on here?

10:48.181 --> 10:50.515
Isn't anyone
gonna say anything?

10:50.550 --> 10:51.850
Yeah.

10:52.418 --> 10:53.952
<i>Gesundheit.</i>

10:56.656 --> 10:59.658
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)
